Description: Three fragments of undyed cotton string and cord. The shortest fragment is 50mm long, has 5 knots and consists of 2 's'-spun elements, 'z'-plied. The 60mm long fragment consists of 3 'z'-spun elements, 's'-plied. The longest fragment is 95mm long and is made of 3 elements of the same type as the 60mm fragment. These 3 elements are 's'-spun and then 'z'-plied.
Bibliographic references: Adams et al 1999 / Kulubnarti III: The Cemeteries (p. 62)
